    "Html": "Hello,<br>\r\n<p><span>\r\n<br>\r\nI want to bind DataGrid to collection of objects which have a field of type ObservableCollection&lt;string&gt; (Subs) which I would like to bind to DataGridComboBoxColumn<br>\r\n<br>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;my:DataGrid Margin=&quot;8,9,6,69&quot; Name=&quot;filmsGrid&quot; AutoGenerateColumns=&quot;False&quot; &gt;<br>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;my:DataGrid.Columns&gt;<br>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;my:DataGridComboBoxColumn ItemsSource=&quot;{Binding Path=Subs, Converter={StaticResource TestConverter}}&quot; &gt;&lt;/my:DataGridComboBoxColumn&gt;<br>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;/my:DataGrid.Columns&gt;<br>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;/my:DataGrid&gt;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>The strange thing is that data are not going to ItemsSource (my TestConverter Convert method is not triggered).</span></p>\r\n<p><span>I also tried to use DataGridTemplateColumn like this:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt;line-height:normal\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;DataTemplate x:Key=&quot;ComboTemplate&quot;&gt;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt;line-height:normal\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;ComboBox&nbsp; &nbsp;ItemsSource=&quot;{Binding Path=Subs, Mode=OneTime, Converter={StaticResource TestConverter}}&quot; &gt;&lt;/ComboBox&gt;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;/DataTemplate&gt;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>I works almost because even with Mode set to OneTime the ItemSource is set when I’m scrolling a grid (binding is refreshed and selection on comboboxes is cleared).</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Any ideas on how to simply bind this collection to ComboBox one time??</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n",
